  "description": {
    "original_author": {
      "date": "2021-02-26",
      "name": "Therese Lindberg",
      "organisation": "Cambio CDS",
      "email": "therese.lindberg@cambio.se"
    },
    "lifecycle_state": "Initial",
    "details": {
      "en": {
        "id": "en",
        "purpose": "To calculate the risk of T-MACS.",
        "keywords": [
          "T-MACS",
          "EKG",
          "ischemia",
          "angina",
          "pain",
          "vomiting",
          "sweating",
          "hypotension",
          "troponin",
          "only",
          "manchester",
          "acute",
          "coronary",
          "syndromes",
          "decision",
          "aid"
        ],
        "use": "Use to calculate  the risk of T-MACS in order to rule out acute coronary syndrome.\n\nFormula:\nProbability of ACS (p) = 1/ (1+e^-(1.713E+0.847A+0.607R+1.417V+2.058S+1.208H+0.089T-4.766))\nwhere:\n\n                                                                            No          Yes\n\nE: EKG ischemia                                                  0             1\n\nA: Worsening or crescendo angina                      0             1\n\nR: Pain radiation to the right arm or shoulder      0             1\n\nV: Pain associated with vomiting                         0             1\n\nS: Sweating observed                                         0              1\n\nH: Hypotension                                                   0              1\n\nT: hs-cTnT concentration on arrival                    hs-cTnT value \n\n\nInterpretation:\nProbability                Risk             Interpretation\n<0.02                       Very low       ACS ruled out. Consider discharge.\n≥0.02 and <0.05      Low              Consider serial troponin in ED ward, e.g. 3h troponin; consider discharge if normal.\n≥0.05 and <0.95      Moderate     Serial troponin in general ward and consider stress testing and/or CT coronary angiography thereafter.\n≥0.95                       High             ACS ruled in. Refer to cardiology, treat for ACS.",
        "copyright": "Cambio CDS"
      }
    },
    "other_details": {
      "references": "1. Body R, Carlton E, Sperrin M, Lewis PS, Burrows G, Carley S, McDowell G, Buchan I, Greaves K, Mackway-Jones K. Troponin-only Manchester Acute Coronary Syndromes (T-MACS) decision aid: single biomarker re-derivation and external validation in three cohorts. Emerg Med J. 2017 Jun;34(6):349-356. doi: 10.1136/emermed-2016-205983. Epub 2016 Aug 26. PMID: 27565197; PMCID: PMC5502241."
    }
  },
